  "text": "As shown in ►Fig. 2, with respect to positional relationships, the supraorbital keyhole craniotomy 2 is located anterior to the middle rami, the lateral supraorbital keyhole craniotomy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] is placed between the anterior and middle rami, and the pterional keyhole craniotomy 5 is situated posterior to the whole temporal branch of the facial nerve. In our experience, supraorbital keyhole craniotomies sometimes result in postoperative facial nerve palsy, which resolves in about 6 months. Lan et al 6 reported a patient who presented with descensus of the eyebrow 3 months after undergoing a supraorbital keyhole craniotomy.",
